# Code Conventions (`packages/excalidraw`)

These rules apply to the **editor package** only. Other workspace packages (`common`, `element`, `math`, `utils`) and `excalidraw-app` may differ — follow existing files in the folder you edit.

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- **Props naming**: `type ComponentNameProps = { … }` — use a **`type` alias** for props (same rule as below). Name follows `{ComponentName}Props`.
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer **`type`** over **`interface`** for object shapes, **including component props**. Use **`interface`** only when you need declaration merging or a pattern that genuinely requires `interface` (rare in this codebase).
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify

- Run `yarn test:code` — ESLint must pass (includes `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` and project rules).
- Run `yarn test:other` — Prettier must report no diffs on changed files.
- New UI in `packages/excalidraw`: colocated test file matches `*.test.ts(x)` next to or mirrored per existing patterns in that package.
